description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu said Yahya Sinwar’s elimination could mark “the beginning of the end” of the war in Gaza.
title: Netanyahu praises IDF killing of Hamas leader Sinwar

description: Rita Lifschitz, whose in-laws were kidnapped on Oct. 7, spoke to NBC News’ Erin McLaughlin about her fear that the death of Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar makes the safe release of hostages less likely.
title: Relative of Oct. 7 hostage ‘scared’ after Hamas leader killed by Israel

description: NBC News spoke to civilians in Khan Younis who expressed both regret that Israel had killed Hamas leader Yayha Sinwar, and also hope that the war in Gaza might now be closer to ending.
title: Gazans react to death of Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar

description: Yahya Sinwar, the leader of Hamas and mastermind behind the October 7 attack on Israel, was killed during a "heavy gun battle" in Gaza, according to and Israeli official. NBC News' Matt Bradley has details on the early reports and reaction to Sinwar's death.
title: Israeli official confirms Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar was killed in Gaza

description: The Israeli military says there is a chance that Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar might have died in Gaza when purportedly three members of Hamas were killed. Sinwar was accused of being the architect of the Oct. 7 terror attacks on Israel. NBC News’ Richard Engel reports on the latest developments and investigations into confirming the Hamas leader’s death.
title: Israeli military says Hamas leader Yahya Sinwar possibly killed in Gaza

description: ‘One Direction’ fans are mourning the death of Liam Payne. Officials in Argentina say the British singer-songwriter died after falling from the third-floor balcony of a hotel in Buenos Aires. NBC News’ Brian Balthazar reports on the latest details surrounding the singer’s death.
title: Fans around the world mourn the death of Liam Payne

description: The world has a worsening water crisis and half of all food production will be at risk of failure by the middle of this century.
title: Half of all global food threatened by growing water crisis, report says

description: The Pentagon said the U.S. launched airstrikes against Houthi targets in Yemen with B-2 stealth bombers. The strikes targeted five underground weapons facilities. NBC News' Meagan Fitzgerald reports on the first time that the U.S. military used B-2 stealth bombers against the Iranian-backed Houthis in Yemen.
title: U.S. military uses B-2 bombers to strike Houthi targets in Yemen

description: Facing increasing U.S. pressure to ramp up aid into Gaza and warning that Washington would be “watching,” as Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu held an emergency meeting to discuss the matter on Wednesday.
title: U.S. says it will be 'watching' as Netanyahu holds emergency meeting on increasing aid to Gaza

description: Sydney beaches, including the famous Bondi Beach, were closed to visitors after hundreds of black balls, suspected to be toxic, washed up on the shore.
title: Mysterious tar balls washing up on the shoreline close Sydney's beaches

description: President Joe Biden left Washington for Germany early Thursday for talks on defense, trade and Ukraine.
title: Biden heading to Berlin for talks on defense, trade and Ukraine

description: Genaro Garcia Luna, who led Mexico’s fight against the country’s violent drug trade, was sentenced to more than 38 years in U.S. prison for accepting bribes from the cartels he was supposed to fight.
title: Mexico ex-drug czar sentenced to more than 38 years in U.S. prison over cartel bribes

description: The U.S. military said it conducted multiple, precision strikes on numerous Iran-backed Houthi weapons storage facilities within Houthi-controlled areas of Yemen. B-2 Spirit long-range stealth bombers took part in the operation. Early Today's Jessica Layton has the details.
title: U.S. Air Force and Navy bomb Houthi weapons storage facility in Yemen

description: U.S. B-2 bombers and other aircraft struck five underground Houthi weapons storage locations in parts of Yemen that the Iranian-backed rebel group controls, Secretary of Defense Lloyd Austin said.
title: U.S. strikes Houthi weapons storage facilities in Yemen
